<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 19 at 3:11PM EST  by NWS Chicago</headline>
<description>...Blowing Snow Likely in Open Areas Sunday morning...
* WHAT...Patchy blowing and drifting snow caused by southwest wind
gusts over 30 mph.
* WHERE...Open or rural areas of north-central and east-central
Illinois and northwest Indiana.
* WHEN...Sunday morning.
* IMPACTS...Reduced visibility and lightly snow covered roads due
to blowing and drifting snow, making for locally hazardous
travel. Temperatures rising above freezing by late Sunday
morning should begin to lessen impacts.
* ACTIONS...Allow extra travel time and expect varying road
conditions and visibility in open areas.</description>
